item.description:
Here is an example of instantiating a class using the new operator:
class Person { constructor(name, age) { this.name = name; this.age = age; } } const asian = new Person('Alice', 25); console.log(asian);  As you can see from below, asian is not a class, it is instead, an object:
[object Object] { age: 25, name: &quot;Alice&quot; }  The values of asian are set by the constructor of the Person class.
